<UNK>Eds: Members who used the 2nd item in a0426 PM-Names of Monday, Oct.
9, with a Kansas City, Mo., dateline, are asked to use the following story.</UNK>
<DATELINE>KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Associated Press reported
erroneously on Oct. 9 that Paul Newman ``stood up'' Paramount
Pictures and dozens of television reporters by failing to appear
for interviews on Oct. 7 regarding his new movie ``Fat Man and
Little Boy.''
   Paramont notes that the television reporters had been informed
in advance that Newman would be unable to give interviews that day
because he was working on another film. Newman met the next day, as
planned, for interviews with newspaper, magazine and radio
reporters.
</TEXT>
