<FIRST>r a PM-Lites     10-11 0333</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Lites,0344</SECOND>
<HEAD>On the Light Side</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FORT LAUDERDALE, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A truck thief was apparently
stopped dead in his tracks when he discovered the vehicle was
marked ``Human Remains, Extreme Care.''
   The 24-foot rental truck, stolen early Monday from a casket
company, was abandoned with its cargo, an empty shipping container
for a corpse.
   ``I think they saw `Human Remains' and said, `Oh, Lordy!''' said
Hugh Allgood, owner of Flite-Rite Co. in Fort Lauderdale. ``A lot
of people for some reason are scared of dead bodies.''
   Pointing out that his company makes caskets, Allgood wondered
about the thief's motivation: ``What ... did they think it would
have in the back? Dead fish?''
   Two similar trucks stolen from Hollywood and Fort Lauderdale
this month were stripped of their tires and radios, said Ted
Shipway, safety manager for Ryder Truck Rental in Fort Lauderdale.
   ``Probably because of the cargo, they left it,'' Shipway said.
``They must have seen the (casket) and gotten scared.''
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>SCOTTSDALE, Ariz. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Peggy Rubach, diehard Chicago Cubs fan
and mayor of Mesa, says she is signing up for singing lessons to
make good on a bet with Scottsdale Mayor Herb Drinkwater
   The two last week wagered on whether the San Francisco Giants
would defeat the Cubs in the best-of-seven National League
playoffs. The Giants won the final game 3-2 Monday, winning the
series 4-1.
   Ms. Rubach now has to sing the national anthem in Scottsdale's
ballpark during the Cactus League spring season. The Cubs play at
HoHoKam Park in Mesa and the Giants train at Scottsdale Stadium.
   Drinkwater said he plans to be at the game to record her
singing. ``I'm going to tape it and save it to use against her as
blackmail when I want something,'' he said.
   Ms. Rubach said: ``In order to ensure proper noise-abatement
procedures and to guarantee that my voice lifted in song will not
contribute to any noise pollution, I pledge to take singing lessons
between now and the game.''
