<SECOND>PM-BRF--Child Hero,0162</SECOND>
<HEAD>Little Boy Calls 911 to Save Mother</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 3-year-old boy calmly called 911 to get
help for his mother, who lay on the living room floor choking on a
cough drop, authorities said.
   Jameson Rodgers, whose 4th birthday is Thursday, had been taught
to dial 911 in the event of an emergency. So he ran to the
telephone his parents had mounted low on the bathroom wall for his
use, said his father, Michael, 26.
   Jameson told fire dispatchers Tuesday night his 32-year-old
mother, Peggy, was on the floor and couldn't breathe, said fire
Battalion Chief Lon Pursell.
   ``She can't come to the phone because she's choking,'' the child
said.
   He didn't know his address, but dispatchers were able to trace
the call and paramedics arrived within a minute, Pursell said.
   Mrs. Rodgers was unconscious, but paramedics were able to
dislodge the cough drop and restore her breathing, Pursell said.
