<HEAD>Burglars Steal 10-Year-Old Boy's Birthday Surprises</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ARP, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Linda Nichols could understand why burglars
stole her videocassette recorder, answering machine, jewelry and
cash, but it was too much when they also took the birthday cake she
bought for her twin sons.
   ``It takes a low person to steal a 10-year-old's birthday
cake,'' Mrs. Nichols said Tuesday.
   One of the twins, Dustin, drew nationwide attention three years
ago during fund-raising efforts to finance a liver transplant to
save his life. He had the operation Feb. 8, 1987, and has been
doing well, Mrs. Nichols said.
   In addition to the cake for Monday's birthdays, Mrs. Nichols had
bought skateboards and cashed a check to take Dustin and Damon to
the state fair in Dallas this weekend. The skateboards were stolen,
along with the cash, leaving her with nothing left to buy
replacement birthday gifts.
   ``I'm mad,'' Mrs. Nichols said.
