<HEAD>Marchers Support Gabon's Leader</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LIBREVILLE, Gabon (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Thousands of people marched through the
capital Wednesday to support President Omar Bongo and denounce an
alleged plot to overthrow him.
   The marchers, mostly supporters of the country's only legal
party, the Gabonese Democratic Party, paraded three miles from the
President Bongo Stadium to the gates of the presidential palace.
   Speakers at a rally before the palace denounced the alleged
conspiracy as ``odious.'' Bongo, who has ruled the West African
