Water Co., in connection with the alleged plot. Others arrested
included the commander of the presidential guard, Mathias
Boussoungou, and a National Gendarmerie colonel, Mabounda Moussavou.
   They are alleged to have contacted European mercenaries and
received financial support from abroad to overthrow Bongo, who
outlawed opposition parties in 1968.
