<HEAD>Brothers Killed in Double-Accident</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GRAND PRAIRIE, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man who was standing near the site
where his brother was fatally hit by a car was struck and killed by
a truck 35 minutes later, police said.
   ``Both accidents were attributed to pedestrians failing to yield
right-of-way to motor vehicles,'' Sgt. Brad Geary said.
   Geary identified the victims as Willie James Wright, 35, who was
hit at 8:45 p.m. Tuesday and William Charles Wright, 33, who was
struck at 9:20 p.m. Both had Fort Worth addresses, but had driver's
licenses from other states.
   Willie and his wife and William with his girlfriend were in a
truck on Interstate 30, Geary said.
   Apparently, Willie and his wife argued and they got out. As the
couple crossed the highway, Willie was hit by a car, Geary said.
When police arrived, they found William and his girlfriend still in
the pickup, apparently unaware of the accident.
   Willie was taken to Dallas-Fort Worth Medical Center, where he
was pronounced dead of head injuries, Geary said.
   Officers laid out flares around the scene. Minutes later, as an
officer was moving the couples' truck, he heard a crash and saw
William had been struck by a truck about 100 feet away. William was
pronounced dead at the scene, Geary said.
