<TEXT>
   A major institutional investor in AMR Corp. says
it has sold all its shares to take advantage of inflated stock
prices in the wake of Donald Trump's $7 billion buyout proposal for
the company that owns American Airlines.
   Since Thursday, when Trump's $120-per-share offer was made
public, Windsor Fund has sold its 425,000 shares, said John B.
Neff, who has managed the fund for 25 years. ``We're out as of
yesterday,'' Neff said Tuesday.
   In New York, Trump pledged to keep AMR headquarters in Fort
