   John G. Smale has announced he is resigning as
chairman and chief executive of Procter &amp; Gamble Co. as part of a
series of top-level personnel moves.
   Smale, 62, made the unexpected announcement to shareholders at
the consumer products giant's annual meeting Tuesday, saying he
wanted to spend more time with his family. He has been the
company's chief executive for the last nine years and leaves office
effective Jan. 2.
