<FIRST>r f BC-Kidder-MerrillLynch     10-11 0198</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Kidder-Merrill Lynch,0205</SECOND>
<HEAD>Kidder Sells Florida, Puerto Rico Offices To Merrill Lynch</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TAMPA, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   New York brokerage firm Kidder Peabody &amp; Co.
says it has sold its retail brokerage operations in Florida and
Puerto Rico to Merrill Lynch, Pierce, Fenner &amp; Smith Inc.
   The sale announced Tuesday includes seven offices in Florida and
one in San Juan.
   Terms of the deal were not disclosed, but a Kidder spokeswoman
said the eight offices accounted for 3 percent of the $956 million
in revenues earned by Kidder Peabody last year.
   The sale means the consolidation of Kidder and Merrill Lynch
offices in cities where each firm has operations. By the end of the
month, the 230 Kidder employees will be working for Merrill Lynch,
said Merrill Lynch spokesman Fred Yager in New York.
   Merrill Lynch _ the largest U.S.-based global financial services
company _ is buying Kidder offices in Miami, Tampa, Fort
Lauderdale, Boca Raton, Winter Park, Sarasota and Jacksonville.
   With the purchase, Merrill Lynch will have 68 offices in Florida
and Puerto Rico. The move gives Florida more Merrill Lynch
brokerages than any other state, Yager said, adding that California
is next in line with 65.
</TEXT>
