<HEAD>Grain Futures Close Mixed; Short-Covering Boosts Beans, Corn</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Most soybean and corn futures prices closed
slightly higher Wednesday on the Chicago Board of Trade as traders
fine-tuned their positions in preparation for Thursday's
Agriculture Department crop report.
   Wheat futures posted modest losses, reflecting a lack of new
export demand.
   The USDA crop report, scheduled for release after Thursday's
close, is expected to indicate slightly larger corn and soybean
harvests than the USDA's September estimates of 1.89 billion
bushels of soybeans and 7.32 billion bushels of corn.
