analyst Conrad Leslie came in slightly below those averages,
prompting some buying of futures this morning.
   Analysts also attributed Wednesday's modest rally to buying
inspired by the soybean market's tumble to 23-month lows on Tuesday.
   ``The markets have really gotten battered around and were
oversold,'' said Joel Karlin, an analyst in Chicago with Research
Department Inc., which provides research services to brokers.
