<SECOND>AM-Oil Prices,0199</SECOND>
<HEAD>Energy Futures Prices Rise</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Energy futures prices closed mostly higher
Wednesday as technical factors dominated the session.
   The November contract for West Texas Intermediate, the benchmark
grade of U.S. crude oil, rose 8 cents to settle at $20.25 a
42-gallon barrel in New York Mercantile Exchange trading following
a 15 cent gain on Tuesday.
   There was no fundamental news to influence trading, said Richard
Kane, an analyst with Merrill Lynch Energy Futures. He described
volume as light to moderate.
   November West Texas Intermediate moved as high as $20.40 a
barrel, but when the contract failed to gain further ground, some
traders decided to take profits late in the day, Kane said.
   Among refined petroleum products traded on the New York Merc,
the November contract for wholesale unleaded gasoine fell 0.26 cent
to 55.73 cents a gallon, but subsequent contract months moved
higher. On Tuesday, the November gasoline contract picked up a full
cent.
   Kane also attributed gasoline's performance to technical factors.
   Home heating oil for November delivery rose 0.17 cent to settle
at 59.81 cents a gallon after rising 0.87 cent the previous session.
</TEXT>
