<FILEID>AP-NR-10-11-89 2044EDT</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Mead     10-11 0274</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Mead,0284</SECOND>
<HEAD>Mead Reports Record Revenues</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DAYTON, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Mead Corp. said Wednesday it set a record
with $1.19 billion in revenue for the quarter ending Oct. 1, but
its earnings for the period declined by more than half compared
with the same quarter last year.
   The revenue figure includes gains from the company's sale in
September of its Release Products Division for $15.5 million.
   Earnings for the third quarter totaled $69.7 million, or $1.06 a
share, compared with earnings of $170.5 million, or $2.56 a share,
for the same quarter last year. Last year's figure included a
$100.9 million gain from the August 1988 sale of a 50 percent stake
in the Brunswick Pulp &amp; Paper Co. of Brunswick, Ga.
   Without the one-time gain, the paper products and electronic
publishing company had comparable earnings of $69.6 million, or
$1.06 a share, for last year's third quarter. Third-quarter revenue
in 1988 totaled $1.17 billion.
   For the first nine months of 1989, Mead reported earnings of
$184.5 million, or $2.83 per share, including the divestiture gain.
Without the gain, those figures would have been $169 million, or
$2.60 per share.
   For the comparable three quarters of 1988, Mead had earnings of
$309.3 million, or $4.69 per share. Excluding the divestiture
gains, its earnings were $197.2 million, or $3.02 per share.
   Mead said plans to open a $550 million specialty paper mill near
Phenix City, Ala., in late 1990.
   ``We foresee continued strong demand for our products through
the fourth quarter, although capacity increases in such areas as
uncoated paper and paperboard have resulted in some softening of
prices,'' Chairman Burnell R. Roberts said.
</TEXT>
