<FILEID>AP-NR-10-11-89 2245EDT</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f BC-Southnet-FoneAmerica     10-11 0145</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Southnet-Fone America,0151</SECOND>
<HEAD>Two Long Distance Telephone Companies Form Joint Venture</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TAMPA, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Southnet Corp. and Fone America Inc., two
companies providing long distance telephone services, have entered
into a letter of intent to form a joint venture, company officials
said Wednesday.
   Tampa-based Southnet and Fone America, a Nevada company, plan to
consolidate and share switching centers, data processing services,
network facilities and billing services, according to a statement
released by the two companies.
   Terms of the agreement are expected to be finalized shortly, the
companies said. Both compete for customers in different geographic
regions.
   ``There is truly a power in numbers aspect in our business and
we have given each other the opportunity to maximize this
advantage,'' said Robert Zradicka, Southnet's chairman and chief
executive officer.
   Southnet Corp. was formed in 1987, while Fone America began
business a year earlier.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
